{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017PauVmckFXR9vMGURGmchX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The PVCs for replicas 3 and 4 were created just 6 minutes ago, so they should be fresh. But the error says \"missing featureCompatibilityVersion document\". This error can happen when:\n1. The data directory was partially initialized (e.g., mongod started, initialized some things, but was killed before completing)\n2. The data directory has stale data from a previous run\n\nSince the PVCs are 6 minutes old (created when I scaled), they should be fresh. But wait - could this be from a previous pod scaling attempt? The `whenScaled: Retain` policy on the StatefulSet means PVCs are kept even when scaled down, so if the pods had previously been created and the data was partially written, the PVCs would retain that state.\nI could either run mongod with `--repair` on those pods to fix the issue, or delete the PVCs and recreate them fresh. Since these are new replicas without any data yet, the safest approach is to delete the PVCs for replicas 3 and 4, then scale down to 3 and back up to 5 so fresh volumes get created. The error itself indicates the data directory has some MongoDB files but is incomplete - missing that critical featureCompatibilityVersion document. I need to be careful about the PVC retention policy—since `whenScaled: Retain` keeps the PVCs even when pods scale down, I can't just scale down and back up expecting fresh storage. The better approach is to scale down first to stop the pods, then manually delete the damaged PVCs for replicas 3 and 4, then scale back up so new PVCs get created with clean data.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":663,"cache_read_input_tokens":38539,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":663},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"936bc9c9-9092-403d-ab9a-8c86016c8439","uuid":"f8962a3f-d405-4096-8ef8-fdc7f9a60000","request_id":"req_011Cc8328yUFX2wVJoCAE6kK"}
