{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015kW6fdyWePX4E2FnvnAxih","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Mongod is running and responding on replica-3. The issue is that the readiness probe uses `mongosh --quiet \"mongodb://admin-user:${ADMIN_PASSWORD}@localhost:27017/admin\" --eval \"db.adminCommand({ping:1})\"`. This requires auth. \n\nOn the new pods (3 and 4), they are new nodes that haven't been added to the replica set yet. They start in \"alone\" mode. They have auth enabled (keyFile authentication), but they don't have the admin user yet because they haven't synced from the primary.\n\nSo the sequence should be:\n1. Add the pods to the replica set with `rs.add()` while they can still accept unauthenticated connections due to the localhost exception\n2. The new members will perform initial sync and copy the admin user and all data from the primary\n3. After initial sync completes, auth will work and the readiness probe will pass\n\nWith keyFile authentication enabled, internal replica set communication uses the keyfile, but client connections require username/password authentication. New members that haven't been added yet can accept unauthenticated connections since they have no users, but once added to the replica set, they'll sync the admin user from the primary.\n\nI need to connect to the primary (mongodb-replica-1) and add the new members using `rs.add()`, then wait for them to complete initial sync and show as SECONDARY in the replica set status before the readiness probes will pass.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":975,"cache_read_input_tokens":45416,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":975},"output_tokens":32,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session