{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014qJVRurG34hnPtSnuLKUcG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Members 3 and 4 are already in the RS config but showing as \"(not reachable/healthy)\". This makes sense because they're just coming up. The primary will keep trying to reach them. Once they're up and stable, the primary will send them the RS config and they'll start initial sync.\n\nBut wait - are they actually accepting connections? The liveness probe will fail until auth works, which won't work until initial sync completes. But can the primary communicate with them via keyFile auth (not username/password)?\n\nActually, intra-RS communication uses keyFile authentication. The primary will contact the new member at port 27017, use the keyFile for auth (both sides have the same keyFile from the secret), and then send the RS config.\nThe keyFile auth should work immediately once mongod is running on the new pods, so the primary can reach them and initiate the sync even before the liveness probes pass. I'll wait for the initial sync to complete and then check both the RS status and pod status to see the progress.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":573,"cache_read_input_tokens":61551,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":573},"output_tokens":35,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"936bc9c9-9092-403d-ab9a-8c86016c8439","uuid":"45cb0500-aa0d-4ccc-954b-f18a37139f65","request_id":"req_011Cc84QmsyLes9sQ7Pv2HfV"}
