{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01BfqsZcHUYiN2fqGXLuS4wD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the primary IS connecting to replica-3 via internalClient (keyFile auth). It's doing `isMaster` checks. Let me look for the RS config transfer.\n\nThe primary is sending `isMaster` commands to the new member using `__system` credentials (internal keyFile auth). The connections are being established. But the RS config isn't being received by the new member.\n\nLooking at the log: connection 1237 was closed by peer, then 1238 was accepted from 10.244.0.22 (the primary is at 10.244.0.20 based on the first message). So there IS communication happening.\nThe critical issue is that the new member has no replset config stored locally - the primary is heartbeating to it but not actually transmitting the RS configuration. In MongoDB's replication protocol, when a new member joins, the primary should send the config to unconfigured members through the heartbeat mechanism, but that's not happening here. I need to check what the primary sees in its own RS config and whether it's properly sending that configuration to the new members.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1740,"cache_read_input_tokens":65048,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1740},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"936bc9c9-9092-403d-ab9a-8c86016c8439","uuid":"0543a36a-7f68-4106-965b-21765b431984","request_id":"req_011Cc84cVreUrxmpbTQD2JiS"}
