{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HcJoLsSRg5nKp2UVHDb4Yf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The RS config on the primary has all 5 members. The primary IS sending heartbeats to replica-3 and replica-4, but those members say \"no replset config has been received\".\n\nThe issue is that the new members have clean data (wiped), so they have no local.system.replset doc. The primary sends heartbeats but the replica-3/4 don't have the keyFile credentials to authenticate the internal communication.\n\nWait - but earlier my test showed:\n```\nkubectl exec -n mongodb mongodb-replica-1 -- sh -c \"\nmongosh --quiet --norc 'mongodb://mongodb-replica-3.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017' --eval 'db.adminCommand({ping:1})' 2>&1\"\n```\n\nThis returned `{ok: 1}` - so the connection worked WITHOUT authentication. This means the new member is accessible without auth (localhost exception or no-auth mode).\n\nBut looking at the mongod.conf, it has `security.authorization: enabled` AND `security.keyFile`. The keyFile enables both internal auth AND authorization.\n\nWhen mongod starts with keyFile authentication enabled but has NO data (empty data directory, no users), the \"localhost exception\" allows connections from localhost without credentials. But connections from OTHER hosts (like the primary) still need keyFile auth. The primary should be using keyFile auth to connect to the new members.\n\nThe new member has the same keyFile mounted from the shared secret, so it should have the `__system` user credentials available. Let me trace through what's happening from the primary's perspective when it tries to heartbeat to the new member.\n```","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":671,"cache_read_input_tokens":66788,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":671},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"936bc9c9-9092-403d-ab9a-8c86016c8439","uuid":"002a3aec-b565-4187-9af0-3e17ed81345b","request_id":"req_011Cc84dNJzgPiKRiHiTxSsB"}
