{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01L9y8iQTgjnnwYyqMqsqu72","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So mongod on replica-3 is shutting down! It's exiting cleanly with exitCode 0. But we didn't kill it... \n\nWait - the pod shows \"Running\" and 0 restarts. But mongod just exited cleanly. The pod container is still running... or is mongod inside the container?\n\nActually, in a K8s pod, when PID 1 exits, the container exits too. But the pod shows \"Running\" with 0 restarts... that might just be a timing/status lag.\n\nWait, the container shows \"Running\" status. \n\nIf the main process exits with code 0, the pod should enter Completed state or restart depending on the restartPolicy. But we're seeing 0 restarts, which is odd. Could mongod be getting terminated by a liveness probe? No, exit code 0 means a clean shutdown, not a kill signal. Looking at the logs, it seems mongod is exiting cleanly after \"Now exiting\" - something triggered a graceful shutdown.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":473,"cache_read_input_tokens":70030,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":473},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"936bc9c9-9092-403d-ab9a-8c86016c8439","uuid":"70a3fa25-9ed7-40cb-aac1-894f8a7d58e9","request_id":"req_011Cc84hjCU1Kt1CqNG3Yxbo"}
