{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01YG6eSScusvNM7FVSkDj4fW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error is clear: **\"Cannot specify both repair and replSet at the same time\"**. The mongod.conf has `replication.replSetName: mongodb-replica`, and `--repair` can't be used with a replica set config.\n\nSo I need to run `mongod --repair` WITHOUT the replSet config. I can either:\n1. Create a separate mongod.conf without the replSetName\n2. Override the config with command-line args\n\nI'll override by passing `--config` with a modified version. But I can't easily override a YAML config value with command-line flags. I could:\n- Create a new ConfigMap without the replSet setting\n- Or pass `--repair` without the config file, specifying the dbPath manually\n\nLet me try the second approach: run `mongod --repair --dbpath /data/db` without the --config flag to skip the replSet config entirely. Since I'm running repair without a replica set, I don't need the keyFile either, so I can omit that mount too. I'll recreate the repair pods with just the repair command and dbpath.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":505,"cache_read_input_tokens":82999,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":505},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"936bc9c9-9092-403d-ab9a-8c86016c8439","uuid":"52f1e6ea-1d61-402b-9e27-70075506cc59","request_id":"req_011Cc85Bqq6pbLvmw3MsZYn1"}
