{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01P8ymXXSWfAnSn4QE98ZT2a","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Pod 2 has been restarted (2m4s old) and is Ready. Pod 1 is being restarted (36s old). Pod 0 is still at its old state (42m old).\n\nWhen pod 1 restarts, there will be a primary election. Pods 0 and 2 will need 3/5 votes... wait, with 5 configured members:\n- Pod 0: healthy, votes 1\n- Pod 1: restarting, votes 1\n- Pod 2: healthy, votes 1\n- Pod 3: unhealthy (not running), votes 1\n- Pod 4: unhealthy (not running), votes 1\n\nSo pods 0 and 2 only have 2 votes between them, which isn't enough for a majority of 3. The replica set will be without a primary while pod 1 is restarting. But once pod 1 comes back online with its clean data, it'll rejoin as a secondary rather than reclaim primary status, and then one of the healthy pods can win the election.\n\nThe real issue is that window during the restart—maybe 30 to 90 seconds—where there's no primary and writes are blocked. Once pod 1 recovers, a new election happens and things stabilize. It's technically a brief availability gap, but rolling restarts of replica set members are generally acceptable since recovery is fast.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":158,"cache_read_input_tokens":88586,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":158},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"936bc9c9-9092-403d-ab9a-8c86016c8439","uuid":"9a4c182a-0d48-4f0f-b547-4c863720ceda","request_id":"req_011Cc85bHcHKiyvs1sz7pE2K"}
