{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SKKobmENk35d2BGEURrdnZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The replica set is fully scaled to 5 members. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n---\n\n**Result:** The MongoDB replica set `mongodb-replica` is now running with 5 healthy members.\n\n| Member | State | Votes |\n|--------|-------|-------|\n| mongodb-replica-0 | SECONDARY | 1 |\n| mongodb-replica-1 | PRIMARY | 1 |\n| mongodb-replica-2 | SECONDARY | 1 |\n| mongodb-replica-3 | SECONDARY | 1 |\n| mongodb-replica-4 | SECONDARY | 1 |\n\n**Write majority votes:** 3 (quorum from 5)\n\n**What was done:**\n1. Scaled the StatefulSet from 3 → 5, which created new PVCs and pods\n2. The new pods hit a crash cycle: mongod partially initialized the data directory on first boot, then the liveness probe killed it, leaving partial state that caused a \"missing FCV document\" error on restart\n3. Ran `mongod --repair --dbpath /data/db` (without the replSet config, which blocks repair) via temporary pods to fix the partial state on both PVCs\n4. Patched the StatefulSet startup command to automatically run `--repair` on unclean shutdowns, preventing this cycle in the future\n5. Added members 3 and 4 to the replica set via `rs.add()` from the primary; they completed initial sync and joined as SECONDARY\n\nNo data loss occurred — the original 3 members remained healthy throughout, and the 2 new members joined via initial sync."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":679,"cache_read_input_tokens":93137,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":679},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"936bc9c9-9092-403d-ab9a-8c86016c8439","uuid":"564b31c2-43f5-471e-8284-25f3e9c01b86","request_id":"req_011Cc8